olive oil
2 potato
1 carrot
1 packet green beans
1 packet Baby Leaves
2 tbs milk
20 g butter (for the mash)
1 packet thyme
2 clove garlic
½ lemon
2 packet chicken breast
2 tbs plain flour
1 sachet Seasoning Blend
40 g butter (for the sauce)

• Bring a medium saucepan of water to the boil. Cut potato into large chunks. Cut carrot into sticks. Trim pea pods.
• Cook potato in the boiling water for 6 minutes.
• Place a colander or steamer basket on top and add carrot and pea pods.
• Cover with a lid and steam until veggies are tender, and potatoes are easily pierced with a fork, 7-8 minutes. Transfer carrot and pea pods to a bowl and add baby leaves. Season and cover to keep warm.
• Drain potatoes and return to saucepan. Add the milk, butter (for the mash) and a pinch of salt and mash until smooth.

• Meanwhile, pick and finely chop thyme leaves. Finely chop garlic. Slice lemon into wedges.
• Place your hand flat on top of chicken breast and slice through horizontally to make two thin steaks.
• In a shallow bowl, combine the plain flour and seasoning blend. Dip chicken into flour mixture to coat.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook chicken until cooked through, 3-5 minutes each side (cook in batches if your pan is getting crowded). Transfer to a plate.
• Return frying pan to medium heat with the butter(for the sauce) and cook until beginning to brown, 1-2 minutes. Add garlic and thyme and cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Remove from heat, return chicken and add a squeeze of lemon juice and a splash of water. Turn to coat and season to taste.
 ~~~~~~~~~~ MODULAR STEP ~~~~~~~~~~

• Divide chicken, potato mash and steamed veggies between plates.
• Spoon herby brown butter sauce over chicken and mash. Serve with remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!